This paper deals with the problem of maximizing a submodular function subject to a cardinality constraint in the data stream model, which is a problem in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the use of techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) to adapt the Sieve-Streaming algorithm. Finally, the paper presents a new approximation algorithm, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
